Ben Hiscox was playing for Stoke Gifford United in Bristol on Saturday . 
  He slipped on the wet ground following tackle and slammed his head on clubhouse wall . 
  Striker was knocked unconscious and rushed to intensive care but died in hospital three days later . 
  Team-mates had gone on to secure 4-1 victory against Mangotsfields Sports . 
  Mr Hiscox described by his club as a 'total legend'